        java.lang.String getNamespace()
        Returns the namespace identifier of this SCTID.
        Returns:
        the namespace identifier or null if this SCTID is a short format ID
        See Also:

      • equalsNamespace

        boolean equalsNamespace(java.lang.String namespace)
        Returns true if the identifiers namespace matches the specified namespace, false otherwise.
        Parameters:
        namespace - the namespace to match (can be null)
        Returns:
        true if the SCTID's namespace matches the specified value

      • hasNamespace

        boolean hasNamespace()
        Returns true if this SCTID has a namespace identifier, false otherwise. Short format IDs do not have namespaces.
        Returns:
        true for long format SCTIDs, false for short format SCTIDs

      • getFormatIdentifier

        int getFormatIdentifier()
        The first digit of the partition identifier. Possible values are:
        • 0 → short format (component originated in the INT release)
        • 1 → long format (component ID has a namespace and orginated in an extension).
        All other values are reserved for future use.
        Returns:
        the format identifier digit

      • getComponentIdentifier

        int getComponentIdentifier()
        The second digit of the partition identifier. Possible values are:
        • 0 → Concept
        • 1 → Description
        • 2 → Relationship
        All other values a reserved for future use.
        Returns:
        the component identifier digit

      • getCheckDigit

        int getCheckDigit()
        Returns the last (check) digit of this SCTID, which can be used to verify the identifier. Note that this is the value that originally came with the instance; it is not recomputed here.
        Returns:
        the check digit, as entered at creation time
        See Also:
        SNOMED Glossary: Check-digit

      • getComponentCategory

        ComponentCategory getComponentCategory()
        Returns the category of the component this SCTID identifiers. The value is derived from the second digit of the partition identifier:
        • 0 → ComponentCategory.CONCEPT
        • 1 → ComponentCategory.DESCRIPTION
        • 2 → ComponentCategory.RELATIONSHIP
        Returns:
        the category of the component identified by this SCTID
